Cao <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uubbax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ubbax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/21/01 1:19:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2096.topic&index=55>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Patch message 02-21-01  *long!*</span><hr size=1> I find it very quaint that most of the other classes get a nice section detailing all of the changes affecting them in the patch message. While the rogue community has to search carefully and thouroughly to find the &quot;nerf&quot; on the evade skill. I wonder why this is? Just because us rogues tend to hide in the shadows and do things in the dark inside the game doesnt mean Verant has to adopt the same mentality outside of the game when supposedly fixing a &quot;bug&quot;. Upon first viewing the proposed change of any kind to the evade skill, every rogue new he or she was doomed from the start. There was no reason to hide the &quot;nerf&quot; deep inside the patch message where most wouldn't read. <br>
<br>
Nadare....why should I, as the highest damage dealer in the game, voluntarily restrict the amount of damage I do in a given encounter?  The evade skill is there to allow me to do all the damage I want to a mob and then get out of harm's way. <br>
<br>
My only hope is that there is a significant decrease in the number of failed evades that most of us experience.  I can handle being put to number 2 or 3 on the hate list versus the bottom as long as my failure rate is signigicantly reduced.  As fast as most rogues climb the hate list in a given encounter it is going to be of the utmost importance that evade fails less often.  The only alternative will be to sit on the sidelines until the mob is at a quarter health then run and stab to your hearts content.  But, who is going to want a group member that only fights 1/4 of the time? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukuurus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kuurus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/21/01 1:37:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2096.topic&index=56>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Patch message 02-21-01  *long!*</span><hr size=1> <i>Nadare....why should I, as the highest damage dealer in the game, voluntarily restrict the amount of damage I do in a given encounter? The evade skill is there to allow me to do all the damage I want to a mob and then get out of harm's way.</i><br>
<br>
Says who?<br>
<br>
Too many rogues view this as it's function because that is what it has evolved into.  This is not and never was its purpose.<br>
<br>
Evade was not implemented to increase a rogue's ability to do damage.  It was conceived and implemented as the survival skill we asked for - to save us from dropping dead all the time.  In danger and low on hps?  Evade and the mob will turn on someone else.  It was never intended for any other purpose and with this fix it still fulfills the original reason it was implemented.<br>
<br>
Your example of sitting out 75 percent of the fight is such a vast exaggeration, it's not worth addressing. <br>
<br>
